HEADWORD: Hardhack
<hw>Hard"hack`</hw> <pr>(-h⟦acr⟧k`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A very astringent shrub (<spn>Spiraea
tomentosa</spn>), common in pastures. The <spn>Potentilla
fruticosa</spn> is also called by this name.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hard-handed</ent>⟦br⟧
